Uganda  recorded at least 14 new
suspected cases of Ebola as the death toll from the outbreak of
the virus rose to 18,  New Vision  reported, citing medical
officials it didnâ€™t identify.  Eleven cases are in the western district of Kibaale, while
three are being treated in the capital, Kampala, after being
transferred from the district, the newspaper said. Four people
died from the outbreak in the district on July 30, while a
patient in the western district of Mbarara is being monitored
for suspected Ebola, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
